  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good tips for essay writing?",
  "response": "Here are some good tips for essay writing:\n\n1. **Understand the prompt:** Make sure you understand what the essay question is asking. If you're unsure, take the time to clarify the prompt before starting to write.\n\n2. **Plan your essay:** Take some time to plan your essay. Create an outline to help you organize your thoughts and stay focused on the topic.\n\n3. **Introduce your topic:** Start your essay with an introduction that introduces the topic and gives the reader a sense of what the essay will be about. A good introduction should also include a thesis statement, which is the main point or argument of the essay.\n\n4. **Use evidence to support your points:** In the body of your essay, use evidence to support the points you are making. This can include data, facts, quotes, and examples. Make sure the evidence is relevant and helps to strengthen your argument.\n\n5. **Write in a clear and concise manner:** Use clear and concise language to express your ideas. Avoid using overly complex words or jargon that may confuse the reader.\n\n6. **Use transitions to connect ideas:** Use transitional phrases and words to help connect your ideas and make your essay flow smoothly. This will make it easier for the reader to follow your argument.\n\n7. **Summarize your main points:** In the conclusion of your essay, summarize the main points you made and restate your thesis. This will help to reinforce your argument and leave the reader with a clear understanding of your position.\n\n8. **Proofread and edit:** Before submitting your essay, take the time to proofread and edit it. Look for any spelling or grammar errors, and make sure the essay flows well and is easy to understand.\n\n9. **Seek feedback:** If possible, seek feedback from others on your essay. This can help you to identify areas for improvement and refine your writing.",
